  "plainText": "Don't Starve\nTogether\nExclusive to:\nTrail Mix\nFood Info\n12.5\n30\n5\nVeggie\nObject Info\n15 Days\nCan be Burned\n40\nCooking Info\nx1 x1 x1 x1\n10 sec\n10\nMiscellaneous\n\"trailmix\"\n“A healthy, natural snack.”\n–Wilson\n“Crunch crunch crunch.”\n–Willow\n“Berries and nuts, berries and nuts!”\n–Wolfgang\n“A handful of sustenance.”\n–Wendy\n“HIGHLY NUTRITIONAL”\n–WX-78\n“Mmmm, natural!”\n–Wickerbottom\n“The perfect snack for a day of chopping.”\n–Woodie\n“Nuts and berries. No bolts.”\n–Maxwell\n“Fascinating. A translucent bag just spontaneously materialized!”\n–Wagstaff\n“Meat öf a nut is nöt true meat.”\n–Wigfrid\n“Crunchy and healthy.”\n–Webber\n“Protein!”\n–Walani\n“Energy food!”\n–Warly\n“I prefer sea snacks.”\n–Woodlegs\n“'TIS MIX OF FOODS”\n–Wilba\n“Belly stuff for belly”\n–Wormwood\n“Ready for a hike.”\n–Wheeler\n“All the energy you need for a long day at work.”\n–Winona\n“Looks chewy. I hate chewing.”\n–Wortox\n“Crunch, crunch, crunch!”\n–Wurt\n“The snack of choice for all intrepid explorers!”\n–Walter\n“I prefer the version that has little bits of candy in it...”\n–Wanda\nTrail Mix is a Fruit Food item introduced in the Reign of Giants DLC. It is cooked in a Crock Pot by combining 1 Roasted Birchnut, 1 Berry, and 1 Fruit.\nTrail Mix is one of the cheapest healing dishes that can be made, restoring more Health than its components, making it a useful early game healing item. However, it restores less total Hunger than its individual ingredients.\nTrail Mix is one of the better healing items for Beefalo, for which it restores 120 health (due to their 4x food health multiplier). It can be made earlier in the game than Dragonpie.\nPrerequisites[edit | edit source]\nRequires:\nRequires:\nRequires:\nExcludes:\nExcludes:\nExcludes:\nExcludes:\nRecipe[edit | edit source]\nExamples[edit | edit source]\n×2\n×3\n×2\n×2\nUsage[edit | edit source]\nGallery[edit | edit source]\nIcon used as emoji for Official Klei Discord\nBy TypeBy Crock Pot Value\nView or edit this template\nFood and Edible Items (by Food Type)\nVeggie\nSeeds\nMeat\nGoodies\nGeneric\nHorrible\nRoughage\nElementals\nBurnt\nRaw\nGears\nGold Dust\nBerry\nWood\nNitre\nLunar Shards\nView or edit this template\nFood and Edible Items (by Food Value)\nMeats\nFishes\nVegetables\nFruits\nMonster Food\nEggs\nDairy\nSweetener\nFrozen\nInedibles\nMagic\nFat\nSeed\nJellyfish\nBone\nFilter\nAntihistamine\nDecoration\nBug\nNo Value Food",
